@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #FFE6CC

title SD-01 - Homepage View Flow

actor Visitor
participant Browser
participant Server
participant Router
participant Controller
participant Model
database Database

Visitor -> Browser: 1. Navigate to homepage\nGET /
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 2. GET /
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 3. Route to Main controller
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 4. Call index() method
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Load homepage data:
    - Latest news (berita)
    - Agenda items
    - Announcements (pengumuman)
    - Videos (playlist)
    - Polling questions
end note

Controller -> Model: 5. view_join('agenda','users','username','id_agenda','DESC',0,4)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 6. SELECT agenda with JOIN users\nORDER BY id_agenda DESC LIMIT 4
activate Database

Database --> Model: 7. Return agenda data array
deactivate Database

Model --> Controller: 8. Return agenda data
deactivate Model

Controller -> Model: 9. view_where_ordering_limit('sekilasinfo',"aktif='Y'",'id_sekilas','DESC',0,3)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 10. SELECT FROM sekilasinfo\nWHERE aktif='Y' ORDER BY id_sekilas DESC LIMIT 3
activate Database

Database --> Model: 11. Return announcements
deactivate Database

Model --> Controller: 12. Return announcements
deactivate Model

Controller -> Model: 13. view_ordering_limit('video','id_video','DESC',0,1)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 14. SELECT FROM video\nORDER BY id_video DESC LIMIT 1
activate Database

Database --> Model: 15. Return latest video
deactivate Database

Model --> Controller: 16. Return video data
deactivate Model

Controller -> Model: 17. view_where_ordering_limit('berita',"status='Y'",'id_berita','DESC',0,5)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 18. SELECT FROM berita\nWHERE status='Y' ORDER BY id_berita DESC LIMIT 5
activate Database

Database --> Model: 19. Return latest news
deactivate Database

Model --> Controller: 20. Return news data
deactivate Model

Controller -> Model: 21. view_where_ordering_limit('poling',"status='Pertanyaan'",'id_poling','DESC',0,1)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 22. SELECT FROM poling\nWHERE status='Pertanyaan' ORDER BY id_poling DESC LIMIT 1
activate Database

Database --> Model: 23. Return polling question
deactivate Database

Model --> Controller: 24. Return polling data
deactivate Model

Controller -> Model: 25. view_where_ordering_limit('poling',"status='Jawaban'",'id_poling','ASC',0,10)
activate Model

Model -> Database: 26. SELECT FROM poling\nWHERE status='Jawaban' ORDER BY id_poling ASC LIMIT 10
activate Database

Database --> Model: 27. Return polling answers
deactivate Database

Model --> Controller: 28. Return polling answers
deactivate Model

note right of Controller
    Prepare view data array:
    - $data['agenda'] = agenda items
    - $data['pengumuman'] = announcements
    - $data['video1'] = latest video
    - $data['terbaru'] = latest news
    - $data['pertanyaan'] = poll question
    - $data['jawaban'] = poll answers
end note

Controller -> Browser: 29. Render template\n(template().'/template', template().'/content', $data)
activate Browser

Browser -> Visitor: 30. Display homepage\nwith news, agenda, videos, polls
deactivate Browser

@enduml
